<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1320316" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ULC.jpg?resize=600%2C419&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="419" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ULC.jpg?resize=300%2C209&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ULC.jpg?resize=58%2C40&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ULC.jpg?resize=260%2C182&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ULC.jpg?resize=186%2C130&amp;ssl=1 186w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ULC.jpg?resize=560%2C391&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/ULC.jpg?w=573&amp;ssl=1 573w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Kogo Council of the United Labour Congress of Nigeria (ULC) on Saturday condemned the recent attack on the Tawari community in Kogi Local Government Area of Kogi State and described the incident as “an act of cowardice.” Gunmen had on January 2 attacked the community and killed over 29 people, burnt down buildings, churches and the palace of the king of the community. A statement issued by the chairman of the union, Opaluwa Eleojo, in Lokoja, said: “The action of those bloodthirsty criminal elements can best be described as an act of cowardice, who could not express their grievance, if any, through the most civilised means, but decided to unleash terror on innocent Nigerians in their sleep. ”The Congress wishes to appreciate the state government for its quick response by fortifying the area with security and the supply of relief materials. “We call on the security agencies in the state to enhance their intelligence network so as to nib in the bud such occurrence in the future. “To the people of Tawari, we sympathise with you.” (NAN)  Vanguard The Governor of Kogi, Alhaji Yahaya Bello, has directed the security agencies in the state to fish out perpetrators of Tawari attack for justice. In a statement by the Governor’s Chief Press Secretary, Mr Onogwu Muhammed, in Lokoja on Friday, the governor said the security agencies should swing into action… January 3, 2020 In "News" Gunmen have killed no fewer than 19 people in Tawari community in the Kogi Local Government Area of Kogi State, burning buildings, including the palace of the king of the community. The Public Relations Officer of the Kogi State Police Command, Mr Williams Anya, confirmed the development in an interview… January 3, 2020 In "News" President Muhammadu Buhari has condemned the murder of 19 people by unknown gunmen attack in Tawari community of Kogi Local Government Area, Kogi State. The president expressed his feelings in a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Malam Garba Shehu, in Abuja on Friday. He advised… January 4, 2020 In "News"